gomodel:SYNGO_2012  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1 \" Autoradiograph of a portion of an endplate labeled with 3H-alpha-bungarotoxin.\nTypically, the grains are distributed over the postjunctional folds\"\n\nIn muscle, alpha-bungarotoxin is a marker of the muscle type nAChR that consists of the α1β1εδ subunits in adult tissue and of the α1β1γδ subunits during fetal development (see attached review in the Additional literature section).\n\n3H-alpha-bungarotoxin is regarded as a marker of all muscle type nAChR subunits.. Experimental description: \"The Ultrastructural Localization and Quantitation of Cholinergic Receptors at the Mouse Motor Endplate \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2012" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

